race.comment: BRIDGE WEDNESDAY (1) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last four starts, the latest when second (19.08) at this track. Solid record here winning two races. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Winning claims. LEG IT LUCY (2) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 4 lengths (19.27) at this track. Likely to be about the mark. ALPHONSE (5) finished well back at this track last time when a 5.5 lengths sixth (19.65) but scored five back at this track (18.83). Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Great chance to atone. SYCAMORE DARNELL (7) can sneak into the finish with the right run.
